empire /ˈɛmpaɪə/

(empires) 

1. N-COUNT An empire is a number of individual nations that are all controlled by the government or ruler of one particular country. 帝国 

例： ...the Roman Empire. …罗马帝国。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to a group of companies controlled by one person as an empire . 企业帝国 

例： ...the global Murdoch media empire. …默多克环球媒体帝国。

